verbose_text: The certain similarity of fennel, Taadol, and chamomile was also seen by hierarchical cluster analysis, which might be due to the presence of comparable amounts of thymol as the major constituent (42.20%, 44.98%, and 34.35%), carvone (14.53%, 15.84%, and 8.12%), and carvacrol (6.71%, 4.12%, and 4.65%) in these 3 aromatic waters.
